"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445904","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>UK Reapers are currently operational in Iraq and Syria. No UK Reapers have been deployed to Libya, and no personnel from UK Reaper Squadrons have been deployed to Libya, Kenya or Somalia in the last three years.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23172 ; 23227","2016-01-26T15:38:31.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445904/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445904/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, in how many countries UK Reapers are currently operational.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445905","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>UK Reapers are currently operational in Iraq and Syria. No UK Reapers have been deployed to Libya, and no personnel from UK Reaper Squadrons have been deployed to Libya, Kenya or Somalia in the last three years.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23171 ; 23227","2016-01-26T15:38:31.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445905/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445905/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Libya: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether UK Reapers have been deployed to Libya.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445906","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>Ministry of Defence personnel in the UK and permanent bases overseas are primarily catered for through a number of multi-activity contracts. Armed Forces personnel serving on operations, exercises and HM Ships and Submarines, are catered for under a single food supply contract with Purple Foodservice Solutions Ltd.</p><p>The cost of feeding Service personnel when on operational deployments and on training exercises varies, depending upon a defined kilocalorie output, which is based on the level of activity being undertaken. Furthermore, the cost will vary across the world reflecting the cost of locally procured food.</p><p>For the vast majority of UK bases, the provision of catering services, including food supply, has been out-sourced to commercial contractors. Service personnel accommodated in these bases &quot;pay as they dine&quot; on a meal by meal basis, but are not obliged to take any meals on site.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-25T16:27:40.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445906/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445906/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Army: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much is spent daily on food on each serving solider.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","23130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445907","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>All food procured for Ministry of Defence (MOD) personnel must comply with MOD food quality standards. These standards comply with all UK and EU production standards, Farm Assurance or equivalent. The Defence Food Quality Standards (DFQS) establishes the minimum quality criteria that the Department requires a supplier to deliver. It sets the standard of what food and ingredients should be provided as part of the contracts to provide nutritious and balanced meals to Service Personnel. The DFQS publication is available online through the gov.uk website at:</p><p>(www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479299/20151006-DFQS-V12-U.pdf).</p><p>The MOD requires all of its food suppliers to comply with both EU and National legislation whilst operating to industry standards and monitors the suppliers' compliance with the DFQS through a combination of product testing and conducting inspections of their premises/production facilities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","23132 ; 23136","2016-01-25T16:28:58.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445907/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445907/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Armed Forces: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the quality and nutritional value of food served to the Armed Forces.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","23131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445908","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>All food procured for Ministry of Defence (MOD) personnel must comply with MOD food quality standards. These standards comply with all UK and EU production standards, Farm Assurance or equivalent. The Defence Food Quality Standards (DFQS) establishes the minimum quality criteria that the Department requires a supplier to deliver. It sets the standard of what food and ingredients should be provided as part of the contracts to provide nutritious and balanced meals to Service Personnel. The DFQS publication is available online through the gov.uk website at:</p><p>(www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479299/20151006-DFQS-V12-U.pdf).</p><p>The MOD requires all of its food suppliers to comply with both EU and National legislation whilst operating to industry standards and monitors the suppliers' compliance with the DFQS through a combination of product testing and conducting inspections of their premises/production facilities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","23131 ; 23136","2016-01-25T16:28:58.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445908/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445908/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Armed Forces: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many inspections have been carried out into the quality of the food served to UK Armed Forces in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","23132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445909","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<p>The Department was notified by Sergeant Blackman's legal team that an application to the Criminal Cases Review Commission was submitted in late 2015. The Department will continue to co-operate fully with Sergeant Blackman's lawyers and will respond expeditiously to any enquiries the Commission may raise with it. This has included the release of the classified documents referred to during the Westminster Hall debate on 16 September 2015.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-01-26T15:41:29.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445909/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445909/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Alexander Blackman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information his Department holds on whether there has been an application to the Criminal Cases Review Commission in respect of the case of Sergeant Blackman.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","23100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445910","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>All food procured for Ministry of Defence (MOD) personnel must comply with MOD food quality standards. These standards comply with all UK and EU production standards, Farm Assurance or equivalent. The Defence Food Quality Standards (DFQS) establishes the minimum quality criteria that the Department requires a supplier to deliver. It sets the standard of what food and ingredients should be provided as part of the contracts to provide nutritious and balanced meals to Service Personnel. The DFQS publication is available online through the gov.uk website at:</p><p>(www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/479299/20151006-DFQS-V12-U.pdf).</p><p>The MOD requires all of its food suppliers to comply with both EU and National legislation whilst operating to industry standards and monitors the suppliers' compliance with the DFQS through a combination of product testing and conducting inspections of their premises/production facilities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","23131 ; 23132","2016-01-25T16:28:58.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445910/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445910/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Armed Forces: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what guidance his Department has issued on the standard, quality and nutritional content of food served to UK armed forces.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","23136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445911","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>None.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","23361","2016-01-26T15:43:25.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445911/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445911/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","France: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions his Department held with its French counterpart on the potential effect on Anglo-French defence contracts of a British exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","23129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445912","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-22","<br /><p>In taking any action in self-defence of the UK, we will take account of well-established principles of self-defence. As the Attorney General pointed out to the Justice Select Committee on 15 September 2015, the Caroline case goes back to the 19th century and was concerned with very different circumstances to those facing us now. However as the Attorney General also made clear, the principles still apply and action in self-defence may be lawful in relation to an attack which has not yet materialised but is imminent. In addition any such action must, like all other action in self-defence, comply with the requirements of necessity and proportionality.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-22T13:34:09.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445912/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445912/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that the Caroline principles are applied to any further targeted killing carried out in self-defence of the UK.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","23236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445913","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>UK Reapers are currently operational in Iraq and Syria. No UK Reapers have been deployed to Libya, and no personnel from UK Reaper Squadrons have been deployed to Libya, Kenya or Somalia in the last three years.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23171 ; 23172","2016-01-26T15:38:31.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445913/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445913/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-19","Africa: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any personnel from UK Reaper Squadrons have been deployed to (a) Libya, (b) Kenya and (c) Somalia in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445914","Department for Education","false","2016-01-27","<p>Due to this agreement with Microsoft, which runs until June 2018, schools stand to save an estimated £30 million. The agreement also gives them greater flexibility in their use of Microsoft software.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-01-27T17:16:22.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445914/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445914/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-19","Schools: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the financial savings to schools in (a) Pendle, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West as a result of its memorandum of understanding with Microsoft announced on 13 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","23167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445915","Department for Education","false","2016-01-22","<p>The department collects the number of teacher vacancies in November each year. The November 2015 collection is still underway as schools, Local Authorities and Academy Trusts have until the end of January 2016 to provide their workforce data.</p><p>The latest available data on the number of vacancies in schools is from the November 2014 School Workforce Census which was published in July 2015 and is available from table 14 at the following web link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014</a></p><p>The published data shows that 0.3% of teaching posts in state funded schools in England were vacant in November 2014.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-01-22T14:22:19.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445915/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445915/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-19","Teachers: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of teaching vacancies at the start of September 2016.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","23198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445916","Department for Education","false","2016-01-22","<p>We have not reduced the funding for any higher education institutions (HEIs) as a consequence of training more teachers than places allocated since 2010-11.</p><br />","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-01-22T14:41:10.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445916/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445916/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-19","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many higher education institutions have had their funding allocated by the National College of Teaching and Leadership reduced as a consequence of training more teachers than places allocated in each academic year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","23197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445917","Department for Education","false","2016-01-22","<p>The number of vacancies in each primary and secondary school is collected as part of the annual November School Workforce Census. The latest national and local authority level statistics were published in July 2015 and are located at the following web link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014</a></p><p>As part of the School Workforce Census collection each state funded school is asked to provide details of the teacher vacancies they have on Census day. Under the Department’s long-standing standard definition, a post is vacant if it is unfilled or temporarily-filled by a teacher on a contract of less than one term. The vacancy must have been advertised, be vacant at the time of the Census and there should still be an intention to fill it.</p><p>The complete guidance on how schools provide School Workforce Census data (including the vacancy data) is available at the following web link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/school-workforce-census" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/school-workforce-census</a></p><p>The published data shows that 0.3% of teaching posts in state funded schools in England were vacant in November 2014.</p><br />","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-01-22T14:40:17.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445917/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445917/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-01-19","Teachers: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what records her Department keeps of the number of unfilled teaching positions at secondary schools (a) nationally and (b) in each local authority area.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","23199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445918","Department for Education","false","2016-01-22","<p>We have changed the approach to initial teacher training (ITT) allocations for the 2016 to 2017 academic year. The National College of Teaching and Leadership (NCTL) will not be allocating a specific number of places to individual organisations for postgraduate ITT courses due to start in the 2016 to 2017 academic year. Instead, eligible schools, school-centred initial teacher training providers (SCITTs) and higher education institutions (HEIs) will be able to recruit (subject to a limited number of controls) as many trainees as they feel they need – until the overall system has recruited sufficient trainees. For 2016/17 the number of places available for HEIs to recruit to (based on the estimate of trainee need as per the teacher supply model) can be found on GOV.UK:</p><ul><li>2016/17 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-itt-recruitment-controls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-itt-recruitment-controls</a>. (Total core postgraduate places available to HEIs = 14,027).</li></ul><p>Prior to 2016/17 we have operated an allocations system for School Direct lead schools, SCITTs and HEIs. For recent years detailed initial and final allocations data for HEIs can be found on GOV.UK:</p><ul><li>2015/16 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2015-to-2016</a>. (Total core postgraduate places allocated to HEIs = 17,066).</li></ul><br /><ul><li>2014/15 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2014-to-2015</a>. (Total core postgraduate places initially allocated to HEIs = 23,095).</li></ul><br /><ul><li>2013/14 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2013-to-2014-final" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/initial-teacher-training-allocations-for-academic-year-2013-to-2014-final</a>. (Total core postgraduate places available to HEIs = 20,005).</li></ul><br /><p>For 2012/13 and earlier published allocations data can be found on the national archives (<a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130423140808/http:/education.gov.uk/rsgateway/DB/TIM/m002013/index.shtml" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130423140808/http:/education.gov.uk/rsgateway/DB/TIM/m002013/index.shtml</a>). An extract detailing the relevant years is shown below. It should be noted that this data cannot be disaggregated into HEIs and non-HEIs but is included for information.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009/10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Primary</strong></p></td><td><p>18,050</p></td><td><p>18,640</p></td><td><p>19,730</p></td><td><p>20,840</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Secondary by subject</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Art</strong></p></td><td><p>595</p></td><td><p>515</p></td><td><p>320</p></td><td><p>320</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Citizenship<sup>3</sup></strong></p></td><td><p>265</p></td><td><p>260</p></td><td><p>185</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Economics, Dance, Media, Performing Arts, Other subjects<sup>5,6</sup></strong></p></td><td><p>295</p></td><td><p>260</p></td><td><p>210</p></td><td><p>220</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>English &amp; Drama</strong></p></td><td><p>2,535</p></td><td><p>2,415</p></td><td><p>2,10