"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445934","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-01-25","<p>The Government has no plans to make an assessment or issue guidance on the import and use of fox urine for the purpose of trail hunting.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","23005","2016-01-25T10:52:36.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445934/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445934/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-01-19","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment her Department has made of the environmental effects of the use of imported fox urine for the purposes of trail hunting.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","23004"
