"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445936","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has not provided any guidance to Europe Direct on the information it provides.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-01-27T14:06:58.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445936/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445936/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what guidance his Department has provided to Europe Direct on the information it provides to people in the UK in the period before the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","22993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445937","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>We regularly raise our concerns about the treatment of Palestinian prisoners with the Israeli authorities, including routine detention of Palestinians from the West Bank in prison inside Israel. We are particularly concerned about the detention of Palestinian children in Israeli prisons. We welcome recent improvements made by the Israeli authorities, including increasing the age of majority from 16 to 18 years old. However, we remain concerned at the number of Palestinian minors held in Israeli detention.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-22T12:38:56.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445937/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445937/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his Israeli counterpart on the transfer of protected persons from the West Bank to prisons inside Israel.","false","Biography information for Mr David Jones","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","23077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445938","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","<p>We do not comment on individual staff matters. There are strict rules about staff declaring outside interests, such as accepting employment or engaging business activities to ensure that there are no conflicts of interest.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-01-27T14:59:28.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445938/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445938/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Larry Covington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether Law Enforcement Adviser, Larry Covington, declared any interests relevant to his employment by his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","22995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445939","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>I have raised the case of Mr Foroughi with President Rouhani and Foreign Minister Zarif. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) spoke to President Rouhani in July 2015 about this case, followed up with a letter on 19 October requesting an update on Mr Foroughi’s welfare and requesting that consular access be granted. The Prime Minister spoke again to President Rouhani on the 19th of January. Mr Foroughi’s case was raised by the Prime Minister in that conversation. We will continue to raise this case, alongside our other consular cases with the Iranian government regularly, at all appropriate levels, including at Ministerial and through our embassy officials in Tehran.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-22T14:03:02.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445939/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445939/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Kamal Foroughi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what further representations his Department plans to make to the Iranian government on securing the release of Kamal Foroughi from imprisonment.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","23102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445940","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","I was concerned to hear reports of academics being arrested for expressing their views on the conflict in southeast Turkey. This included 15 academics from Kocaeli University who have subsequently been released. Our Ambassador in Turkey released a public statement on the issue, expressing concern. We regularly underline the importance of Fundamental Freedoms, including freedom of expression as part of our dialogue with the Turkish government. Freedom of expression and public debate must be respected without fear of intimidation.","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-22T14:04:35.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445940/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445940/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Turkey: Arrests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Turkish government on the arrest of academics (a) in general and (b) at the Kocaeli University in north-western Turkey.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","23103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445941","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","The Arab Partnership was created in 2010 and became a key part of the Government’s response to the Arab Spring. This initiative comprised two parts: the FCO-led Arab Partnership Participation Fund and the DFID-led Arab Partnership Economic Facility. Between 2011 and 2015 the Arab Partnership Participation Fund provided funding totalling £42,803,007 for projects in the region. In financial year 2014/15 the fund provided £10,512,791 of which £8,498,003 was allocated to projects promoting human rights and democracy across the Middle East and North Africa region.","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-22T14:06:56.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445941/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445941/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Arab Partnership Participation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the cost to the public purse was of the promotion of democracy and human rights through the Arab Partnership Fund in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","23104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445942","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>As I said in my published article marking Human Rights Day, human rights work &quot;is the responsibility of all British diplomats&quot;. Calculating the proportion of each UK diplomat's time spent on human rights work, and their associated cost, would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-22T14:08:21.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445942/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445942/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many full-time equivalent staff in his Department were employed to work on human rights in 2014-15; and what the cost of these employees was to the public purse.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","23105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445943","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","<p>We are extremely concerned about the growing threat from extremist groups in Libya, including Daesh. The recent attacks in the Oil Crescent and Zliten in western Libya show the threat that these groups pose to the stability of Libya and the region, and potentially to the UK and our interests. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) spoke to Prime Minister Designate, Fayez al-Serraj, on 10 January to stress the importance of the Government of National Accord forming quickly, and to emphasise the UK Government’s commitment to supporting the new government to tackle the threats from Daesh and people smuggling.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-27T15:01:12.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445943/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445943/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Libya: Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Libyan government on tackling the spread of Daesh","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445944","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-26","<p>The Government opposes the use of the death penalty in all circumstances as a matter of principle but I have no plans to issue prescriptive guidance to posts on how they represent the Government’s position on the death penalty. UK Heads of Mission are best placed to judge what the most effective course of action will be, according to local circumstances.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2016-01-26T16:41:11.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445944/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445944/answer","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445944/answer/previousversion/40680","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Capital Punishment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what guidance (a) has been issued and (b) his Department plans to issue in 2016 to UK diplomats in states with the death penalty on representing the Government's position on the use of that penalty.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","23106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445945","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","The UK provided £14 million to support the 2013 Constituent Assembly elections in Nepal. This consisted of support to provide an environment conducive to free, fair and inclusive elections and technical support.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-01-27T15:36:29.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445945/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445945/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Nepal: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support the Government has given to the government of Nepal on the conduct of elections.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445946","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","<p>Foreign and Commonwealth Office ministers regularly discuss Libya with their Egyptian counterparts, as part of the united international effort to assist the formation of a government in Libya that can deliver stability, security, and prosperity for the Libyan people. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond) continues ongoing discussions of Libya with his Egyptian counterpart, Minister for Foreign Affairs Sameh Shoukhry. They previously discussed the subject in meetings in September and November.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-27T15:03:57.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445946/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445946/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Egypt: Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterparts in the Egyptian government on Libya.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445947","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-26","<p>We are aware of the case of Hassam Mushiema and we have raised it with the Government of Bahrain. We continue to encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments and to appropriately address all reports of ill-treatment of detainees. In parallel, we encourage all those with concerns about their treatment in detention to report these directly to the Ombudsman.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-01-26T15:36:46.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445947/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445947/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Hassan Mushaima","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Bahraini government on the provision of medical treatment to Mr Hassam Mushiema.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","23110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445948","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-22","<p>Any individual or organisation can apply to the fund. All parties that submit bids are subject to due diligence checks to ensure they have the capacity/ability to deliver their proposed project in line with the funds objecitves. This applies to all Foreign and Commonwealth Office programme funds. Bids will be rigorously assessed against the criteria set out in our programme guidance and strategy, available online.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-01-22T13:50:47.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445948/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445948/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Magna Carta Fund for Human Rights and Democracy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether trade union groups based abroad will be eligible to bid for funding from the Magna Carta Fund for Human Rights and Democracy.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","23162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445949","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-27","<p>The ongoing violence in the predominantly Kurdish areas of south east Turkey is extremely concerning. The Kurdistan Workers’ Party (PKK) continues to kill members of the Turkish police service and security forces in violent terrorist attacks. The Turkish Government has responded by striking PKK targets in Turkey and Northern Iraq. They have also launched large-scale security operations involving curfews in some towns and cities in order to clear them of suspected terrorists.</p><p>We are aware of reports of civilian casualties in the region, and a worsening humanitarian situation in certain areas in south east Turkey. The Turkish Government have said that 48 civilians lost their lives in clashes between 23 July and 23 December 2015. They also said that 93,000 people have fled their homes. We also understand that there have been investigations launched against elected officials and politicians. Any such investigations should be undertaken transparently and fully respect the rule of law.</p><p>We believe Turkey has a legitimate right to defend itself against the PKK, whose attacks we condemn as we condemn all terrorism. Our thoughts are with the victims of these attacks, and the civilians who have been caught up in the violence. As in any conflict, civilian casualties should be avoided and human rights need to be fully protected. We have been clear, in public and private, that PKK violence must end and we support a return to the peace process, in the interests of Turkey and the region. We stand ready to help in any way we can.</p><p>We continue to monitor the situation closely. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge and our Ambassador to Turkey have emphasised to the Turkish government the need to respect human rights, avoid civilian casualties and return to the peace process. I raised these issues with my Turkish counterpart the last time we met in August 2015.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","23184 ; 23185 ; 23186 ; 23187 ; 23188 ; 23189 ; 23190","2016-01-27T14:12:44.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445949/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445949/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-19","Turkey: Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the treatment of democratically-elected officials in predominantly Kurdish areas of Turkey.","false","Biography information for Natalie McGarry","Glasgow East","Natalie McGarry","23183"
