"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445976","Department of Health","false","2016-01-27","<p>I responded to the hon. Member’s letter of 19 November 2015 on 21 January 2016.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-01-27T17:24:16.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445976/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445976/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-19","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he intends to answer the letter to him dated 19 November 2015 with regard to Mr R Short.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","22987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445977","Department of Health","false","2016-01-27","<p>Health Education England is responsible for providing national leadership on education, training and workforce development in the National Health Service in England. The professional regulators, such as the General Medical Council, set the standards and outcomes for education and training and approve training curricula. Higher Education Institutions are responsible for ensuring the programmes they provide allow students to meet these standards and outcomes. Royal colleges, such as the Royal College of General Practitioners also have responsibility for developing curricula for doctors and nurses, in particular postgraduate curricula. This process ensures that healthcare professionals have the knowledge, skills and attitudes to provide high quality patient care, including in pain management, which is a required competency of all healthcare professionals.</p><br /><p>Many patients with chronic pain can be successfully supported and managed through routine primary and secondary care pain management services. It is important that patients with the most serious pain management issues are able to access specialist care. A patient whose pain is particularly difficult to manage may be referred to a specialised pain management service. Under the care of an expert multidisciplinary team, patients may be offered specialised pain management programmes specifically and more complex drug treatments.</p><br /><p>To support clinicians in the management of pain, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has published several clinical guidelines on the treatment and management of different types of pain, such as migraine and back pain, as well as technical guidance on specific treatments, such as the use of opiates in palliative care and deep brain stimulation for chronic pain.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","23020","2016-01-27T12:15:31.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445977/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445977/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-19","Pain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to improve the care of, and better respond to, NHS patients with chronic pain.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","23064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445978","Department of Health","false","2016-01-22","<p>In accordance with the Terms of Reference agreed at the start of the programme when he was Minister, the expert panel submitted the findings and recommendations of the Mutuals in Health Pathfinder Programme to the Government through an internal report.</p><br /><p>This is currently being considered by the Government.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-01-22T10:05:26.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445978/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445978/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-19","NHS: Mutual Societies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to publish the report on the Mutuals in Health Pathfinder Programme.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","23017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445979","Department of Health","false","2016-01-27","<p>The consultation on payment schemes for people given infected blood products was launched on 21 January 2016, on the same day I made an oral statement to the House, <em>Official Report</em>, columns 1583-85. The consultation is available at gov.uk.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-01-27T15:29:52.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445979/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/445979/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-19","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 5 January 2016 to Question 20185, on what date his Department plans to publish the consultation and make an announcement on payment schemes for people affected by contaminated blood products.","false","Biography information for Kevin Hollinrake","Thirsk and Malton","Kevin Hollinrake","23006"
